==English==

===Pronunciation===
*{{AHD|mə-shēnʹ shŏp'}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A facility that has [[machine tool|machine tools]] for working with [[metal|metals]] or other relatively hard materials, such as some polymers. Various kinds of machine shops make and repair all types of metal objects, from machine tools, dies, and molds to mass-produced parts such as screws, pistons, or gears.

===See also===
*''General machine shops'' are [[public]] [[business]]es that perform work for customers.
*''Dedicated machine shops'' are part of a larger company. They perform work for the company and are not open to the public.

===See also===
:''Machine shops use a wide variety of metal-working tools, including:''
* [[drill]]s
* [[lathe]]s
* [[milling machine]]s
* [[press]]es
* [[cut]]ting and [[welding]] equipment
* [[grind]]ing and [[polish]]ing machines